# Jira tasks and updates

For **my tasks**, **assigned work**, or **update/assign** Jira: use project script from **project root** (`.env` loaded). Script: `scripts/jira-api.mjs`. Never read or expose `.env`.

Output is **slim by default** (avatarUrls, self, iconUrl, expand, renderedFields stripped). Pass `--raw` for the full Jira blob.

## Commands (project root)

| Action | Command |
|--------|--------|
| My issues | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs search "assignee = currentUser() ORDER BY updated DESC"` |
| Current user (accountId) | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs me` |
| One issue | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs get DPH-123` |
| Multiple issues (1 API call) | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs batch DPH-1 DPH-2 DPH-3` |
| Children of a story | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs subtasks DPH-100` |
| JQL search | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs search "JQL"` |
| Subtask (create) | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs create-subtask DPH-123 "Summary" [accountId]` |
| Assign | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs assign DPH-123 <accountId>` |
| Update fields | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs update DPH-123 '{"summary":"..."}'` |
| Transition | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs transition DPH-123 "In Progress"` |
| Comment | `node scripts/jira-api.mjs comment DPH-123 "text"` |

Prefer `batch` over looping `get`. Prefer `subtasks` over manual JQL for children.

## Behavior

- Run command, use JSON to answer (summarise, list keys).
- Assign: confirm before running. Subtasks: show summary/details for confirmation before creating.
